In this article, President Trump delivers remarks on the shooting that took place earlier that morning at a practice session for the annual charity baseball game. He expresses gratitude for the heroic actions of the Capitol Police officers who took down the gunman and commends the first responders from Alexandria Police, Fire, and Rescue. Trump also pledges his support to Congressman Steve Scalise, who was shot and is now in stable condition at the hospital. He emphasizes the importance of unity and working together for the common good in times like these. The President concludes by urging people to cherish their loved ones and remember those who serve and keep the country safe.